The Prague transport company will also deliver a chip card for the first time on Wednesday
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008, you will enter the history of the Prague Transport Company on the date the first passenger enters the metros, trams and buses, who will have an electronic coupon in his pocket instead of a paper ticket.
The coupon is currently available to about 100,000 people who have an Opencard chip card.
Passengers can purchase a 30-day, 90-day and annual coupon (valid as of 1 January 2009) and at the same time they can save on their chip cards in the information centers and branches of the Transport Company at the Muzeum, M<0xC5><0xAF>stek, Nádra<0xC5><0xBE><0xC3><0xAD> Hole<0xC5><0xA1>ovice, And<0xC4><0x9B>l, Roztyly, Let<0xC5><0x88>any, Kobyhlaly, Rajka
Coupons can be purchased online from yesterday via the website of the Transport Company www.dpp.cz.
The service was used by more than 400 customers until the afternoon hours.
Those who start using online trading can permanently forget the publishing windows of the metro stations, where they have regularly had to go through long lines for line tickets.
The coupon can be purchased online and saved to the Opencard card in one of the thirteen accounts of the City Library.
“In these locations, passengers have access to a desk with trained servers to help those interested in online shopping and save their purchased coupons on their cards,” said Martin Opatrn<0xC3><0xBD>, a project spokesman.
In addition to libraries, electronic coupons can also be saved to Opencard in self-service vending machines equipped in some hallways.
What do these machines look like?
They are red, they are reminiscent of ticket managers and passengers may have noticed them on Roztyly, Bud<0xC4><0x9B>jovicka, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská metro stations.
“There are currently five of them in the city, but by the end of the year it should be eighty,” Opatrn<0xC3><0xBD> added.
The coupon is automatically checked instead of the driver.
It’s easy to manage the automatics starting tomorrow.
It is enough to just insert the Opencard chip card and the previously paid coupon will be saved by itself.
From tomorrow, electronic coupons will be valid not only in the capital, but also around it.
So on the trains and bus lines around the city from 300 to 499, with which the inhabitants of the districts of Central Bohemia travel mainly to the capital.
