MP3 players can cause hearing loss
It can cause permanent hearing loss by listening to portable player devices for longer and at high volume, such as MP3 devices -
In a report published in Brussels, the European Commission, based on the opinion published today by the Scientific Committee on New and Newly Identified Health Risks (SCENIHR).
"It turns out that 5 to 10 percent of people who listen to their portable music player for more than an hour per day for five years may suffer permanent hearing loss," the statement said.
